1
00:00:41,070 --> 00:00:41,900
This is…

2
00:00:41,970 --> 00:00:43,430
How does the melody sound?

3
00:00:51,650 --> 00:00:52,610
Is this music?

4
00:01:04,360 --> 00:01:05,330
Just kidding.

5
00:01:05,940 --> 00:01:07,540
The melody is pretty smooth,

6
00:01:07,780 --> 00:01:09,370
especially the chorus.

7
00:01:10,470 --> 00:01:11,630
It has a strong sense of imagery.

8
00:01:11,630 --> 00:01:13,360
After what I told you last time,

9
00:01:13,440 --> 00:01:15,340
I went home and got inspired,

10
00:01:15,640 --> 00:01:16,720
so I wrote this melody.

11
00:01:16,720 --> 00:01:17,850
You're so talented.

12
00:01:18,490 --> 00:01:20,180
As expected of my good apprentice.

13
00:01:20,180 --> 00:01:21,880
Since you said my melody

14
00:01:21,880 --> 00:01:22,980
is so visual,

15
00:01:22,980 --> 00:01:23,850
then,

16
00:01:24,480 --> 00:01:26,410
do you want to write the lyrics with me?

17
00:01:26,410 --> 00:01:27,820
I want you to sing the main section,

18
00:01:27,820 --> 00:01:29,220
and I'll take the chorus.

19
00:01:36,270 --> 00:01:37,509
Let's give it a try.

20
00:01:39,520 --> 00:01:40,979
You even brought a guitar.

21
00:01:41,310 --> 00:01:42,700
I borrowed it from the school.

22
00:01:42,700 --> 00:01:44,090
I don't have my own.

23
00:01:55,310 --> 00:01:58,570
When your fingertips press
the seventh fret of the guitar,

24
00:01:58,810 --> 00:02:01,490
the sound suddenly
becomes very unfamiliar.

25
00:02:02,450 --> 00:02:04,550
Could that be a new movement?

26
00:02:09,620 --> 00:02:10,460
A heartbeat

27
00:02:11,060 --> 00:02:12,460
doesn't short-circuit.

28
00:02:13,060 --> 00:02:13,900
It should be…

29
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:15,600
A flutter.

30
00:02:23,610 --> 00:02:24,670
Just take it.

31
00:02:24,910 --> 00:02:25,740
Otherwise,

32
00:02:25,740 --> 00:02:27,940
you'll get wet when you wait for the car.

33
00:02:28,110 --> 00:02:28,910
Besides...

34
00:02:29,240 --> 00:02:30,700
It's quite cold like this.

35
00:02:37,390 --> 00:02:38,420
Senior!

36
00:02:46,490 --> 00:02:47,820
Why are you so nice to me?

37
00:02:49,260 --> 00:02:50,060
Senior,

38
00:02:50,340 --> 00:02:51,300
taking care of me

39
00:02:51,640 --> 00:02:52,870
makes me happy.

40
00:02:53,030 --> 00:02:54,030
Taking care of you

41
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:55,670
feels the same to me.

42
00:02:56,160 --> 00:02:57,490
Isn't this perfect?

43
00:03:07,260 --> 00:03:08,470
There's a veterinary clinic ahead.

44
00:03:08,470 --> 00:03:09,730
It might still be open.

45
00:03:15,390 --> 00:03:17,460
Even if they're not by my side, it's okay.

46
00:03:17,460 --> 00:03:18,380
At least

47
00:03:18,730 --> 00:03:20,460
when I need them,

48
00:03:20,630 --> 00:03:21,630
they are the ones

49
00:03:21,630 --> 00:03:23,430
that I can see when I turn around.

50
00:03:24,130 --> 00:03:25,260
They are in my heart.

51
00:03:25,730 --> 00:03:26,630
That's enough.

52
00:03:31,230 --> 00:03:32,120
Tell me.

53
00:03:32,450 --> 00:03:33,579
What did I do wrong?

54
00:03:33,579 --> 00:03:34,540
You did nothing wrong.

55
00:03:34,540 --> 00:03:36,140
Then why are you avoiding me?

56
00:03:36,880 --> 00:03:38,480
Because I fell for you.

57
00:04:11,250 --> 00:04:13,350
We're going to the aquarium tomorrow.

58
00:04:13,350 --> 00:04:14,810
Remember to dress up a bit.

59
00:04:26,390 --> 00:04:30,730
[The Seventh Fret:
A Voice No Longer Familiar]

60
00:04:45,610 --> 00:04:46,610
Auntie,

61
00:04:47,370 --> 00:04:48,330
I'm heading out.

62
00:04:55,560 --> 00:04:56,360
It's nothing.

63
00:04:57,159 --> 00:04:58,760
I'll be home a bit late today.

64
00:04:58,890 --> 00:04:59,630
Bye.

65
00:05:10,520 --> 00:05:12,750
[Hello Ms. Chen Ruojiu, your endowment
insurance policy is about to mature.]

66
00:06:01,590 --> 00:06:02,030
[xpark]

67
00:06:22,940 --> 00:06:24,340
Put your hands like this.

68
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:25,840
Lean forward,

69
00:06:25,860 --> 00:06:26,590
like me.

70
00:06:27,280 --> 00:06:28,880
Look, we move when they move.

71
00:06:29,590 --> 00:06:31,590
I don't think they're going to move.

72
00:06:32,790 --> 00:06:33,970
Let's go.

73
00:06:34,340 --> 00:06:34,940
No.

74
00:06:37,030 --> 00:06:39,159
Then let's waddle over like penguins.

75
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:40,409
You go first.

76
00:06:40,730 --> 00:06:41,159
Okay.

77
00:06:41,159 --> 00:06:41,900
You have to keep up with me.

78
00:06:41,900 --> 00:06:43,430
Okay, I'll keep up with you.

79
00:06:48,670 --> 00:06:49,810
Why didn't you learn?

80
00:06:49,810 --> 00:06:50,370
Go.

81
00:06:50,370 --> 00:06:51,070
There's something over there.

82
00:06:51,070 --> 00:06:51,510
There's something else over there.

83
00:06:51,510 --> 00:06:52,370
-Hurry up and learn with me.
-There's something else over there.

84
00:06:52,370 --> 00:06:54,370
There's something else over there.

85
00:06:54,810 --> 00:06:56,100
So cute. Look.

86
00:06:57,750 --> 00:06:58,780
You're cute too.

87
00:07:02,750 --> 00:07:03,350
Just as cute.

88
00:07:03,350 --> 00:07:05,150
There's another one over there.

89
00:07:19,950 --> 00:07:20,780
Hello.

90
00:07:21,740 --> 00:07:22,470
Excuse me.

91
00:07:22,700 --> 00:07:23,810
I just saw that you two

92
00:07:23,810 --> 00:07:24,910
seem to have a good relationship.

93
00:07:24,910 --> 00:07:26,740
We have a couple's wishing event.

94
00:07:26,740 --> 00:07:28,000
Would you like to join?

95
00:07:28,940 --> 00:07:29,410
We're not...

96
00:07:29,410 --> 00:07:29,940
Sure.

97
00:07:30,880 --> 00:07:32,140
Just treat it as a game.

98
00:07:32,250 --> 00:07:33,380
Don't overthink it.

99
00:07:34,620 --> 00:07:35,250
Okay.

100
00:07:35,250 --> 00:07:37,550
Now hold hands,

101
00:07:38,090 --> 00:07:39,020
close your eyes,

102
00:07:39,420 --> 00:07:40,720
and silently

103
00:07:41,890 --> 00:07:43,159
make a wish

104
00:07:43,159 --> 00:07:44,260
in your heart.

105
00:07:46,860 --> 00:07:47,430
Okay.

106
00:07:47,450 --> 00:07:48,730
Open your eyes.

107
00:07:48,730 --> 00:07:50,930
I'll take a photo of this moment for you.

108
00:07:51,370 --> 00:07:52,070
Your wishes

109
00:07:52,070 --> 00:07:53,870
and your love will all come true.

110
00:07:59,140 --> 00:08:01,930
[Heartbeats and Underwater Shadows]

111
00:08:06,650 --> 00:08:07,220
Aren't you curious

112
00:08:07,220 --> 00:08:08,820
about what I just wished for?

113
00:08:09,820 --> 00:08:10,750
No.

114
00:08:10,950 --> 00:08:12,450
Wishes should be kept
in the bottom of your heart.

115
00:08:12,450 --> 00:08:13,860
And I believe

116
00:08:13,860 --> 00:08:15,660
they will definitely come true.

117
00:08:15,690 --> 00:08:17,090
Was it something like

118
00:08:17,290 --> 00:08:18,890
getting first place in exams

119
00:08:18,990 --> 00:08:20,630
or traveling around the world?

120
00:08:20,630 --> 00:08:21,460
Of course not.

121
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:22,760
My wish is...

122
00:08:27,130 --> 00:08:28,530
I'm not going to tell you.

123
00:08:33,039 --> 00:08:33,909
This is for you.

124
00:08:35,580 --> 00:08:36,780
You keep this for now.

125
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:38,850
This is

126
00:08:38,950 --> 00:08:40,409
our first photo together.

127
00:08:41,419 --> 00:08:42,120
Oh, right.

128
00:08:42,350 --> 00:08:44,210
This is our first photo together.

129
00:08:44,220 --> 00:08:45,450
You keep this for now.

130
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:47,060
From now on,

131
00:08:47,990 --> 00:08:49,190
all the rest are mine.

132
00:08:52,890 --> 00:08:53,460
Okay.

133
00:08:54,230 --> 00:08:55,660
I'll take this one first.

134
00:08:56,330 --> 00:08:58,190
The rest from now on are all yours.

135
00:09:06,110 --> 00:09:06,770
Be careful.

136
00:09:22,930 --> 00:09:23,650
[Good Friends Guitar Instrument Store]

137
00:09:23,670 --> 00:09:24,580
[You have a new message]

138
00:09:26,860 --> 00:09:27,400
Okay.

139
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,330
What do you mean by that?

140
00:09:30,350 --> 00:09:31,460
Wait for me here.

141
00:09:32,430 --> 00:09:33,370
I'll be right back.

142
00:09:33,370 --> 00:09:34,360
So mysterious.

143
00:10:16,810 --> 00:10:17,750
Boss.

144
00:10:18,710 --> 00:10:19,550
Welcome.

145
00:10:20,980 --> 00:10:22,350
Where is this?

146
00:10:23,180 --> 00:10:24,050
I'm not...

147
00:10:24,050 --> 00:10:26,510
This is the boundary
between life and death.

148
00:10:27,660 --> 00:10:29,460
You can call it

149
00:10:30,760 --> 00:10:31,830
the Six Gates.

150
00:10:34,010 --> 00:10:35,480
Everyone dies,

151
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:37,690
but only those with unresolved wishes

152
00:10:38,170 --> 00:10:40,350
and lingering regrets

153
00:10:40,700 --> 00:10:41,870
end up here.

154
00:10:43,870 --> 00:10:45,410
So what you're saying is

155
00:10:48,090 --> 00:10:49,350
I'm dead?

156
00:11:46,830 --> 00:11:51,640
[Smile After Tears]

157
00:12:01,710 --> 00:12:04,690
[Alarm Clock]

158
00:12:15,730 --> 00:12:16,630
Morning.

159
00:12:18,080 --> 00:12:19,320
[Maybe it's because you're
in your senior year of high school]

160
00:12:19,340 --> 00:12:20,220
[The club has been
on break these past few days]

161
00:12:20,240 --> 00:12:21,090
[I still work part-time every night]

162
00:12:21,120 --> 00:12:21,710
[And I told you]

163
00:12:21,730 --> 00:12:22,410
[Wei is dating someone again]

164
00:12:41,560 --> 00:12:43,220
I bought you a new wrist wrap.

165
00:12:43,540 --> 00:12:44,980
Change it if you want.

166
00:12:57,740 --> 00:12:58,410
Junjia.

167
00:12:58,840 --> 00:12:59,410
Morning.

168
00:12:59,830 --> 00:13:00,380
Morning.

169
00:13:01,410 --> 00:13:02,140
You didn't

170
00:13:02,140 --> 00:13:03,340
ride your bike today.

171
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:06,300
It's broken.

172
00:13:07,810 --> 00:13:09,710
We are surrounded by the sea.

173
00:13:10,280 --> 00:13:12,120
There are sandy coasts and rocky coasts.

174
00:13:12,120 --> 00:13:14,380
Do you know the difference between them?

175
00:13:14,690 --> 00:13:17,490
The wrist wrap you gave me is badly worn.

176
00:13:18,090 --> 00:13:20,490
I've been reluctant
to ride my bike lately.

177
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:30,970
Junjia,

178
00:13:32,120 --> 00:13:33,300
why are you here?

179
00:13:35,800 --> 00:13:36,670
Senior,

180
00:13:39,420 --> 00:13:40,550
I'm sorting through

181
00:13:41,540 --> 00:13:43,200
photos of his favorite, Galu.

182
00:13:44,920 --> 00:13:46,220
Tie

183
00:13:47,120 --> 00:13:47,960
has already taken several days off

184
00:13:47,960 --> 00:13:49,220
because he is so sad.

185
00:13:54,070 --> 00:13:54,940
What about you?

186
00:13:57,950 --> 00:13:58,920
Just like this.

187
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:05,010
You know

188
00:14:05,450 --> 00:14:06,650
what that guy is like.

189
00:14:10,640 --> 00:14:12,880
Moody, unpredictable.

190
00:14:13,580 --> 00:14:15,070
He does whatever he wants.

191
00:14:15,830 --> 00:14:17,640
No one can stop him.

192
00:14:18,220 --> 00:14:18,720
He.

193
00:14:18,750 --> 00:14:19,290
Well…

194
00:14:19,310 --> 00:14:20,690
-I mean
-He just got here. He doesn't know.

195
00:14:20,690 --> 00:14:21,820
everybody out.

196
00:14:21,840 --> 00:14:22,340
Okay.

197
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:24,010
From now on,

198
00:14:24,040 --> 00:14:25,440
you are our guitarist.

199
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:29,050
How long are you planning
to keep practicing like this?

200
00:14:29,050 --> 00:14:30,600
Then I'll drink

201
00:14:30,670 --> 00:14:32,040
this one.

202
00:14:32,060 --> 00:14:32,980
That's mine,

203
00:14:35,310 --> 00:14:36,310
not yours.

204
00:14:37,460 --> 00:14:38,520
Even...

205
00:14:40,700 --> 00:14:42,280
Even now that he's gone,

206
00:14:44,180 --> 00:14:45,550
he didn't say goodbye.

207
00:14:50,970 --> 00:14:51,800
No.

208
00:14:52,680 --> 00:14:53,780
I know

209
00:14:53,980 --> 00:14:56,390
He has always been by our side.

210
00:15:58,940 --> 00:16:00,920
[Learning has no end]

211
00:16:07,660 --> 00:16:10,440
The last word is describe.

212
00:16:10,970 --> 00:16:12,170
Come on, read after me.

213
00:16:12,170 --> 00:16:13,390
Describe.

214
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:14,640
Describe.

215
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:15,100
Good.

216
00:16:15,100 --> 00:16:16,640
It's a verb.

217
00:16:35,060 --> 00:16:36,290
He,

218
00:16:37,260 --> 00:16:39,790
I often see you standing here
and spacing out.

219
00:16:48,800 --> 00:16:50,840
Is this your favorite scenery?

220
00:16:52,370 --> 00:16:53,430
Be careful.

221
00:16:54,710 --> 00:16:55,680
What are you doing here?

222
00:16:55,680 --> 00:16:56,610
It's dangerous.

223
00:17:08,319 --> 00:17:09,160
Come down.

224
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:19,400
Why did you climb so high?

225
00:17:19,630 --> 00:17:21,359
-What if you...
-What if I jump?

226
00:17:25,329 --> 00:17:26,599
I'm not kidding.

227
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:28,329
Do you know it's dangerous?

228
00:17:28,620 --> 00:17:29,990
Then you know

229
00:17:30,210 --> 00:17:31,450
that I'm not that fragile.

230
00:17:31,450 --> 00:17:32,040
But

231
00:17:33,580 --> 00:17:34,620
once something happens,

232
00:17:34,620 --> 00:17:36,180
there's no turning back.

233
00:17:37,600 --> 00:17:38,830
In terms of many things,

234
00:17:38,830 --> 00:17:40,490
we don't have a second chance.

235
00:17:45,090 --> 00:17:46,030
I'm fine.

236
00:17:47,230 --> 00:17:47,960
Let's go.

237
00:17:48,280 --> 00:17:49,350
Class is starting.

238
00:18:02,270 --> 00:18:03,400
Welcome.

239
00:18:05,840 --> 00:18:06,800
Are you

240
00:18:06,830 --> 00:18:07,940
Jiayi?

241
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:21,870
I didn't come to find you.

242
00:18:29,670 --> 00:18:30,800
Do you know

243
00:18:30,800 --> 00:18:32,110
you're very happy?

244
00:18:36,190 --> 00:18:37,870
Every time I meet He,

245
00:18:37,950 --> 00:18:39,610
all he ever talks about is you.

246
00:18:40,460 --> 00:18:41,180
"Jiayi

247
00:18:41,180 --> 00:18:43,780
rushed the beat again
at band practice today."

248
00:18:43,820 --> 00:18:46,220
"Jiayi is really good at ordering drinks."

249
00:18:47,130 --> 00:18:48,590
"Jiayi is always smiling.

250
00:18:48,590 --> 00:18:50,250
Doesn't his mouth get tired?"

251
00:18:51,800 --> 00:18:54,070
Every time school comes up,

252
00:18:54,790 --> 00:18:56,330
you were the only one

253
00:18:56,360 --> 00:18:57,560
he ever talked about.

254
00:18:58,520 --> 00:18:59,920
He really

255
00:19:01,430 --> 00:19:02,730
liked you a lot.

256
00:19:07,900 --> 00:19:08,900
I'm sorry.

257
00:19:12,800 --> 00:19:14,380
I'm really sorry.

258
00:19:18,340 --> 00:19:18,940
Wait.

259
00:19:19,390 --> 00:19:20,520
Don't tell me

260
00:19:20,940 --> 00:19:23,340
you actually believe those school rumors?

261
00:19:27,180 --> 00:19:28,980
You didn't do anyone wrong,

262
00:19:29,190 --> 00:19:31,120
and you didn't do my brother wrong.

263
00:19:35,170 --> 00:19:36,040
Your brother?

264
00:19:36,700 --> 00:19:37,800
He...

265
00:19:37,820 --> 00:19:39,250
He's my cousin.

266
00:19:41,160 --> 00:19:43,960
Then why does everyone
at school say you two are...

267
00:19:46,780 --> 00:19:48,240
There's a reason for that.

268
00:19:56,550 --> 00:19:57,400
Gu Yitong!

269
00:19:57,590 --> 00:19:58,800
What's going on now?

270
00:19:58,990 --> 00:19:59,450
I...

271
00:19:59,810 --> 00:20:00,940
You're Jin Xianzuo?

272
00:20:01,250 --> 00:20:02,120
Who are you?

273
00:20:02,150 --> 00:20:03,330
I'm her boyfriend.

274
00:20:04,470 --> 00:20:05,530
What are you doing?

275
00:20:05,900 --> 00:20:07,030
What are you saying?

276
00:20:07,480 --> 00:20:09,010
Gu Yitong is my girlfriend.

277
00:20:12,700 --> 00:20:13,310
What do you want?

278
00:20:13,310 --> 00:20:14,280
What do you want?

279
00:20:14,310 --> 00:20:15,600
You didn't answer my calls;
I couldn't find you!

280
00:20:15,600 --> 00:20:17,000
What do you want exactly?

281
00:20:24,390 --> 00:20:25,000
Yitong,

282
00:20:26,050 --> 00:20:26,940
I was wrong.

283
00:20:28,490 --> 00:20:29,920
I shouldn't have hit you.

284
00:20:30,610 --> 00:20:31,740
Let's make up, okay?

285
00:20:33,390 --> 00:20:34,830
She doesn't have to answer you.

286
00:20:34,830 --> 00:20:36,170
This has nothing to do with her.

287
00:20:36,170 --> 00:20:38,300
Talk to me if you have something to say.

288
00:20:38,910 --> 00:20:40,500
So you're cheating on me now?

289
00:20:40,500 --> 00:20:42,030
Or are you dumping me?

290
00:20:47,360 --> 00:20:49,070
Enough, Jin Xianzuo!

291
00:20:51,970 --> 00:20:53,620
Gu Yitong is mine.

292
00:20:53,810 --> 00:20:55,360
With an ex-boyfriend like you,

293
00:20:55,360 --> 00:20:57,020
she's better off without you.

294
00:20:59,830 --> 00:21:01,200
Stop hitting him!

295
00:21:01,260 --> 00:21:02,080
Go away!

296
00:21:04,360 --> 00:21:05,390
To gather evidence,

297
00:21:05,390 --> 00:21:07,630
my brother didn't even fight back.

298
00:21:22,200 --> 00:21:23,520
Psycho!

299
00:21:30,980 --> 00:21:32,370
But that day,

300
00:21:32,750 --> 00:21:33,790
I also found out

301
00:21:33,790 --> 00:21:35,190
that my brother was sick.

302
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:37,400
Let's go to the hospital.

303
00:21:43,260 --> 00:21:44,500
You didn't know?

304
00:21:49,880 --> 00:21:52,150
I can't believe he didn't tell you.

305
00:22:04,760 --> 00:22:05,660
It seems

306
00:22:05,680 --> 00:22:07,690
he must have given
a lot of happiness and joy

307
00:22:07,690 --> 00:22:08,530
to you.

308
00:22:16,250 --> 00:22:17,620
My brother smiled a lot

309
00:22:17,660 --> 00:22:19,230
during that time.

310
00:22:22,220 --> 00:22:22,840
Thank you,

311
00:22:22,870 --> 00:22:23,590
Jiayi.

312
00:22:39,340 --> 00:22:40,290
It seems

313
00:22:40,360 --> 00:22:42,170
he must've shared a lot of

314
00:22:42,190 --> 00:22:43,920
his happiness and joy with you.

315
00:22:46,380 --> 00:22:47,820
My brother smiled a lot

316
00:22:47,840 --> 00:22:49,340
during that time.

317
00:22:52,880 --> 00:22:54,620
Familiar smiles.

318
00:22:55,180 --> 00:22:56,630
Familiar figures.

319
00:22:58,140 --> 00:23:00,840
They left all their joy and happiness

320
00:23:01,040 --> 00:23:02,140
to me.

321
00:23:03,700 --> 00:23:05,900
[Heartbeats and Underwater Shadows]

322
00:23:04,240 --> 00:23:05,450
But

323
00:23:06,910 --> 00:23:09,310
in the end,
I couldn't hold on to any of them.

324
00:23:09,720 --> 00:23:11,520
I've already experienced loss.

325
00:23:12,550 --> 00:23:14,760
Now, facing loss again,

326
00:23:17,820 --> 00:23:19,040
I realized

327
00:23:19,660 --> 00:23:21,390
that what hurts more than death

328
00:23:21,560 --> 00:23:22,960
is having to keep living.

329
00:23:28,420 --> 00:23:29,900
Are you saying

330
00:23:32,690 --> 00:23:34,030
that I'm dead?

331
00:23:43,140 --> 00:23:44,340
How is that possible?

332
00:23:45,290 --> 00:23:47,020
Are you kidding me?

333
00:23:51,640 --> 00:23:53,440
Jiayi is still waiting for me.

334
00:23:54,790 --> 00:23:56,090
I can't die.

335
00:23:56,120 --> 00:23:57,210
I can't.

336
00:23:59,670 --> 00:24:01,270
Jiayi.

337
00:24:08,570 --> 00:24:12,310
[Preview of the Next Episode]

338
00:24:09,830 --> 00:24:11,640
Those whom I've lost,

339
00:24:12,430 --> 00:24:14,330
I will never be able to get them back.

340
00:24:14,330 --> 00:24:15,660
Your uncle passed away.

341
00:24:16,560 --> 00:24:18,220
Your parents passed away too.

342
00:24:18,720 --> 00:24:20,030
